HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 402
BY REPRESENTATIVE PHELPS
A RESOLUTION
To commend Loretta Wiley for completing a master's degree at the age of seventy-five.
WHEREAS, Loretta Wiley is a Christian, mother, grandmother, and widow who
resides in the unincorporated community of Princeton in Bossier Parish, Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Wiley attended elementary and high school in the Bossier Parish
School System; in 1967, she had the privilege of being a member of the first class enrolled
at Southern University at Shreveport; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Wiley completed her undergraduate education at Southern
University at Baton Rouge and graduated in 1971 with a bachelor of science degree in
secondary education; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Wiley resumed her education in 2006, enrolling at Louisiana Tech
University to pursue a master's degree; after a pause in her educational journey, she re-
enrolled at Louisiana Tech as a post-baccalaureate student in 2021 to pursue an
undergraduate certification in forensic psychology; and
WHEREAS, after completing the undergraduate certificate, Ms. Wiley enrolled as
a graduate student and earned a graduate certificate in domestic violence; she continued her
higher educational pursuits by working on a master's degree in human services, which she
received on May 24, 2025; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Wiley served as a substitute teacher prior to and throughout her
graduate studies, and she has supported her students and served her community with
dedication and care; she will continue to serve in this capacity for the remainder of her
professional career; and
